Parts of Sweetwaters, in Pietermaritzburg, will experience a nine-hour power outage due to a planned overhead line maintenance this week. According to a notice issued by Msunduzi on Monday, the electricity will be switched off during the installation of a pole transformer PT 856 and PT 848. “The electricity supply interruption is scheduled to start on Tuesday, 31 May, from 8am to 5pm and an alternative date is Thursday, 2 June, from 8am to 5pm,” reads the notice. Areas that will be affected include parts of Sweetwaters, Madwaleni, Mbanjwa, Mvumbulukwana and Mayekeleni. Residents can contact Nonzwakazi on 067 029 5409 if they have any queries.